        "@value": "https://catalogo.beniculturali.it/detail/HistoricOrArtisticProperty/0900289175"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "beastiary:part_wings",
      "@type": "beast:AnatomicalPart",
      "beast:embodiesImaginarySymbol": {
        "@id": "beast:ascensional_symbol"
      },
      "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Wings are the ascensional instrument par excellence: in Durand's scheme they directly contradict gravity and embody the heroic upward flight away from temporal degradation. Durand names the wing explicitly as \"the ascensional instrument that contradicts gravity,\" making this the textbook case."
      }
    },
